	<div class="oss-cards">
		<article class="oss-card">
			<header class="oss-card__header">
				<span class="oss-card__icon">{% icon "code-slash" %}</span>
				<h3 class="oss-card__title"><a href="{{ apiSpecs.voiceml.urlPath }}">VoiceML</a></h3>
			</header>
			<p class="oss-card__description">Twilio-compatible voice REST API. Drop-in for existing Twilio SDKs; same wire shape, same webhook signing, same pagination envelope. Update your voice URL to <code>voiceml.voicetel.com</code> and your existing markup works unchanged.</p>
			<p class="oss-card__url"><a href="{{ apiSpecs.voiceml.urlPath }}">voicetel.com{{ apiSpecs.voiceml.urlPath }}</a></p>
			<p class="oss-card__action"><a href="/voiceml/validator/">Validate markup &rarr;</a></p>
		</article>

		<article class="oss-card">
			<header class="oss-card__header">
				<span class="oss-card__icon">{% icon "tag" %}</span>
				<h3 class="oss-card__title"><a href="{{ apiSpecs['v2.2'].urlPath }}">VoiceTel API {{ apiSpecs['v2.2'].version }}</a></h3>
			</header>
			<p class="oss-card__description">Consolidated REST reference covering account, authentication, ACL, gateways, numbers, CNAM/LRN lookups, e911, iNumbering, and support tickets — every customer-facing platform endpoint in a single OpenAPI spec.</p>
			<p class="oss-card__url"><a href="{{ apiSpecs['v2.2'].urlPath }}">voicetel.com{{ apiSpecs['v2.2'].urlPath }}</a></p>
			<p class="oss-card__action"><a href="/docs/api/v2.2/playground/">Try in playground &rarr;</a></p>
		</article>

		<article class="oss-card">
			<header class="oss-card__header">
				<span class="oss-card__icon">{% icon "shield-check" %}</span>
				<h3 class="oss-card__title"><a href="{{ apiSpecs.csp.urlPath }}">10DLC Campaign Registry</a></h3>
			</header>
			<p class="oss-card__description">Proxy to The Campaign Registry's Campaign Service Provider (CSP) API for brand registration, campaign vetting, webhooks, and appeals. Required before A2P messaging traffic can run.</p>
			<p class="oss-card__url"><a href="{{ apiSpecs.csp.urlPath }}">voicetel.com{{ apiSpecs.csp.urlPath }}</a></p>
			<p class="oss-card__action"><a href="/docs/api/v7.8/csp/playground/">Try in playground &rarr;</a></p>
		</article>
	</div>
